Usage: report_fanin [-help] [-nosplit] [-pin_levels <levels>]
                    -to <pins, ports, nets>
                    [-trace_through {case_disable|user_disable|all}]
                    [-view <viewname>] [> <fileName>] [>> <fileName>]

-help                       # Prints out the command usage
-nosplit                    # Formatting option (bool, optional)
-pin_levels <levels>        # Depth of traversal (int, optional)
-to <pins, ports, nets>     # List or collection of pins, ports or nets for
                            # which fanin is desired. (string, required)
-trace_through {case_disable|user_disable|all}
                            # Option to traverse disabled arcs (string, optional)
-view <viewname>            # View name for which disabled arcs shall be
                            # considered. (string, optional)
> <fileName>                # Name of the output file.
                            # (redirect_operator, optional)
>> <fileName>               # Name of the output file.
                            # (redirect_operator, optional)